Reasoning: The paper deals with combinatorial properties of directed graphs and their recursive definitions, which are typical topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The concepts of directed path-width and directed tree-width are also relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the application of these concepts to directed co-graphs, which are related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
